<h3><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">Announcement/Alert</span></strong></h3>
<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Immigration and Tax Scam Affecting International Scholars</span><br /><span style="color: #ff0000;">There has been a recent increase in reports of fraud involving individuals posing as immigration&nbsp;and tax officials requesting personal and bank information from international scholars. Please&nbsp;remember that the International Scholar Center, Internal Revenue Service (IRS), and U.S.&nbsp;immigration officials will never request credit card, Social Security, or banking information over&nbsp;the phone. Refer to the U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS) and Federal Trade&nbsp;Commission websites for tips on how to avoid scams or report any instances of fraud.</span><br /><a href="http://www.uscis.gov/avoid-scams/report-immigration-scams">http://www.uscis.gov/avoid-scams/report-immigration-scams</a><br /><a href="http://www.consumer.ftc.gov/articles/0076-phone-scams">http://www.consumer.ftc.gov/articles/0076-phone-scams</a></p>-->
